passages.text: The MSCI REIT Index underperformed the S&P 500 over the past week by - 5bp (2.0% vs 2.1%). The best performing asset class over the past week was Hotels (6.4%) while the worst performing asset class was Free Stdg (- 1.9%).
The best performing stocks in our coverage universe over the past week were: PEB (12.4%), DEI (8.3%), MAC (8.3%), BXP (7.9%), and KRC (7.4%).
The worst performing stocks in our coverage universe over the past week were FCPT (- 0.5%), SUI (- 1.0%), ELS (- 1.2%), ADC (- 1.9%), and VTR (- 2.3%).

REITs trade at 101% of NAV, versus the long- term average of 99%. On adjusted funds from operations (AFFO) basis, REITs trade at a forward AFFO multiple of 20.7x versus the long- term average of 17.7x.

The dividend yield on the REIT sector stands at 3.95% and the spread to the 10- year Treasury yield (4.20%) is currently - 25bp, while the spread to BAA Corp Bonds stands at - 215bp. Relative to the S&P 500, the dividend yield spread is 281bp (3.95% versus 1.14%), compared to the long- term average of 323bp.
Short interest (as a % of the float) for the EVR ISI REITs sector stood at 3.8% as of August 15, 8bp up from two weeks earlier and 10bp up from one month earlier.

Please see the analyst certification and important disclosures on page 34 of this report. Evercore ISI and affiliates do and seek to do business with companies covered in its research reports. Investors should be aware that the firm may have a conflict of interest that could affect the objectivity of this report.
